 NGOZI OKORIE THREE policemen, who were on their way to their assignment posts at Oporoma, headquarters of the Southern Ijaw Local Government Area of Bayelsa State, have reportedly drowned. They were said to have met their untimely death, on the eve of the Saturday bye-election in the state. The incident happened when the speedboat that was conveying the deceased to their destination reportedly capsized. Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Asinim Butswat, confirmed the accident, noting that the number of casualties had not been ascertained.  